By Sumaila Ogbaje ABUJA – The burial programme of the Chief of Army Staff (COAS), late Lt.-Gen. Ibrahim Attahiru and six other senior officers has been slated for Saturday in Abuja. The deceased lost their lives in an air mishap in Kaduna on Friday. The Director, Army Public Relations, Brig.-Gen. Mohammed Yerima, said the event would commence at the National Mosque and National Christian Centre, Abuja by 10am respectively. Yerima said that the interment for the late COAS and 6 other senior officers would take place at the National Military Cemetery, Abuja by 1pm. In all, 11 military officers died in the military plane crash in Kaduna on Friday. The full list, according to a dispatch by PRNigeria, is as follows: LT GEN I ATTAHIRUBRIG GEN MI ABDULKADIRBRIG GEN OLAYINKABRIG GEN KULIYAMAJ LA HAYATMAJ HAMZASGT UMARCREW FLT LT TO ASANIYIFLT LT AA OLUFADESGT ADESINA11. ACM OYEDEPO •Lt. Gen Ibrahim Attahiru By Sumaila Ogbaje ABUJA - The Nigerian Army has confirmed death of its Chief, Lt.-Gen. Ibrahim Attahiru and 10 others, in an ill-fated NAF aircraft near Kaduna International Airport on Friday, saying he was a highly decorated officer. The Director, Army Public Relations, Brig.-Gen. Mohammed Yerima,… In "Top Stories" Abuja - The ill fated military jet that crashed on Friday in Kaduna has top military officers in the entourage of the General Ibrahim Attahiru on board. The plane crashed close to Kaduna airport where the late Chief of Army Staff was billed to commission a project in one of… In "Top Stories" ....Atiku says it's a dark day for the nation By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja - The Nigerian Army has announced the death of its Chief of Army Staff, Lieutenant General Ibrahim Attahiru in a plane crash on Friday evening. The Army disclosed this in a statement signed by the Director Army… In "Top Stories"